18/08/2005
MRAKOVICI, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Following a meeting of state and entity government officials in Mrakovici on Wednesday (17 August), Republika Srpska Prime Minister Pero Bukejlovic said there may be a final agreement on key BiH police reforms by the end of August. Although the Mrakovici talks did not result in concrete accords, Bukejlovic suggested that the entities' negotiators showed a willingness to find a mutually acceptable solution. The talks continue next week in Mostar. (Nezavisne novine, Dnevni avaz - 18/08/05; AFP, RTRS, PBS BiH - 17/08/05)
